		</name>
    <questiontext format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p class="HELM_exercise">Exercise</p>
<p>Given that <span class="math inline">\(z={@z@}\)</span>, <span class="math inline">\(w={@w@}\)</span> , which of the points below represent \({@s@}z+{@t@}w\) on an Argand diagram.</p>
<figure class="HELM_figure"><img src="@@PLUGINFILE@@/Complex%20Numbers%20Argand%20plot.svg" alt="Argand diagram with points A, B, C, D" width="300" height="238" class="img-responsive atto_image_button_text-bottom"><br></figure>
<p><br></p>
<p>\({@s@}z+{@t@}w=\)[[input:ans1]] [[validation:ans1]]&nbsp;[[feedback:prt1]]<br></p>]]></text>
		</questiontext>
    <generalfeedback format="moodle_auto_format">
				<text><![CDATA[<p>We are given that \(z={@z@}\) and&nbsp;\(w={@w@}\). Then,&nbsp;&nbsp;\({@s@}z+{@t@}w={@s@}({@z@})+{@t@}({@w@}).\) This is the point \({@cor1@}\) on the Argand diagram.</p>]]></text>
		</generalfeedback>
